; catalogue; biology, dispersal power, ecology, geographic distribution, references).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="58BE20F2E30FFFE1FF6DF9F3913CF8F2" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="101B7379E30FFFE1FF6DF9F3913CF8F2" blockId="36.[192,1441,1538,1882]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FF6DF9F39350F9B1" bold="true" box="[192,316,1538,1562]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FEE6F9F3900BF9B1" authorityName=": Netolitzky" authorityYear="1931" box="[331,615,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FEE6F9F3900BF9B1" box="[331,615,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Bembidion nesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FC17F9F39601F9B1" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[954,1133,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callipeplum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FC17F9F39601F9B1" box="[954,1133,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">B. callipeplum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has previously been synonymized with it by 
<bibRefCitation id="74350E88E30FFFE1FE45F9D390C2F992" author="Lindroth, C. H." box="[488,686,1569,1594]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" pagination="161 - 198" refId="ref33972" refString="Lindroth, C. H. 1976. Genus Bembidion Latreille (Coleoptera: Carabidae) in New Zealand: a revision. New Zealand Journal of Zoology 3: 161 - 198." type="journal article" year="1976">Lindroth (1976)</bibRefCitation>
. Examination of the 
<typeStatus id="CF1FCDDBE30FFFE1FC02F9D39672F991" box="[943,1054,1570,1594]" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FBE9F9D3969AF991" authorityName=": Netolitzky" authorityYear="1931" box="[1092,1270,1570,1594]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FBE9F9D3969AF991" box="[1092,1270,1570,1594]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">B. nesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revealed it to be a separate species from 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FDBCF9B390A9F9F1" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[529,709,1602,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callipeplum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FDBCF9B39048F9F2" box="[529,548,1602,1625]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FD99F9B390A9F9F1" box="[564,709,1602,1626]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">callipeplum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition to diagnostic characters of the male genitalia, 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FF6DF993931FF9D1" authorityName=": Netolitzky" authorityYear="1931" box="[192,371,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FF6DF993931FF9D1" box="[192,371,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">B. nesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the following features that clearly separate it from 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FB98F9939686F9D1" authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1878" box="[1077,1258,1634,1658]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="callipeplum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FB98F9939624F9D2" box="[1077,1096,1634,1657]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FBF4F9939686F9D1" box="[1113,1258,1634,1658]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">callipeplum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: body slender, larger (length 
<quantity id="D75CDE9CE30FFFE1FEDEF970906AF931" box="[371,518,1665,1690]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.25" metricValueMax="4.9" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" unit="mm" value="4.25" valueMax="4.9" valueMin="3.6">3.6–4.9 mm</quantity>
); microsculpture transverse, obsolete on disc of head and pronotum, feeble on elytra; antennae subfiliform (segments 8–10 stout), pale testaceous; legs also pale testaceous; pronotum with sides strongly sinuate posteriorly and posterolateral angles acute, projected laterally; elytra widest before middle, with smaller light brown markings. 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FC4AF913976FF951" authorityName=": Netolitzky" authorityYear="1931" box="[999,1283,1762,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nesophilum">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FC4AF913976FF951" box="[999,1283,1762,1786]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Bembidion nesophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the northernmost part of the North Island (ND, AK, WO). This species is found in association with members of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="D7A408FAE30FFFE1FDACF8D39011F891" authorityName="Lindroth" authorityYear="1980" box="[513,637,1826,1850]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Zecillenus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="22D0AF6BE30FFFE1FDACF8D39011F891" box="[513,637,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="35">Zecillenus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the sandy banks of coastal estuarine streams; it hides during the day in the sand, at a certain distance from water.
</paragraph>
